    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Includes correspondence and other documents primarily from W.L. Calver and Reginald P. Bolton, including background information on the committee and its role in awakening a "keener sense of interest in American history," particularly the American Revolution; a list of military and other buttons, acquired from Leslie G. Hilborn, which provides a detailed list of which uniform the button belonged to, such as British or American soldier, regiment or corps, rank, and condition of button; a history of brass buttons from Fort George, Niagara-on-the-Lake, Ontario, early 1800s; and observations by Bolton on the Ross Mansion in Essex, NY, and Chimney Point, Vt.</field>
